/wiki/Vadim_Pronskiy: Vadim Pronskiy (born 4 June 1998) is a Kazakh cyclist, who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam Astana.
/wiki/Boris_Car%C3%A8ne: Boris Carène (born 7 December 1985 in Pointe-à-Pitre, Guadeloupe) is a French professional road bicycle racer who currently rides for amateur team Carène Development. In 2011, he was the winner of the 61st edition of the Tour de Guadeloupe. He won the 2012 Caribbean Cycling Championships in Antigua.
/wiki/Francisco_Mancebo: Francisco Mancebo Pérez (born 9 March 1976 in Madrid) is a Spanish professional cyclist. He initially rode for team Illes Balears–Banesto, but moved to AG2R Prévoyance in 2006.
/wiki/Yonathan_Salinas: Yonathan Jesús Salinas Duque (born 31 May 1990 in Rubio, Venezuela) is a Venezuelan cyclist riding for Deportivo Tachira–JHS.
/wiki/S%C3%A9bastien_Fournet-Fayard: Sébastien Fournet-Fayard (born 25 April 1985) is a French road cyclist, who currently rides for Pro Immo Nicolas Roux.
/wiki/Juan_Murillo: Juan Engelberth Murillo Ortíz (born August 1, 1982) is a Venezuelan professional road racing cyclist.
/wiki/%C5%BDydr%C5%ABnas_Savickas_(cycli: Žydrūnas Savickas (born 28 April 1991) is a Lithuanian former racing cyclist. He rode at the 2014 and the 2015 UCI Road World Championships.
/wiki/Damien_Monier: Damien Monier (born August 27, 1982 in Clermont-Ferrand) is a French professional road bicycle racer for UCI Continental team Aisan Racing Team.
/wiki/Jos%C3%A9_Chac%C3%B3n_D%C3%ADaz: José Isidro Chacón Díaz (born  January 27, 1977 in Táriba) is a Venezuelan professional racing cyclist.
/wiki/Diego_Mil%C3%A1n: Diego Milán Jiménez (born July 10, 1985) is a Spanish-born professional road bicycle racer, who competes for Inteja Imca–Ridea. Milán has also competed for Acqua & Sapone–Caffè Mokambo, Caja Rural and Differdange–Losch. Since 2012, Milán competes under a licence from the Dominican Republic, having been born in Spain.
/wiki/Antonio_Pedrero: Antonio Pedrero López (born October 23, 1991 in Terrassa) is a Spanish cyclist, who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam Movistar Team. He was named in the startlist for the 2017 Vuelta a España. In May 2018, he was named in the startlist for the 2018 Giro d'Italia.
/wiki/John_Nava_(cyclist): John Alberto Nava Carvajar (born 6 October 1978) is a male professional road racing cyclist from Venezuela.
/wiki/Pierre_Lebreton: Pierre Lebréton was a French tennis player. He competed in the men's singles and doubles events at the 1900 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Miyataka_Shimizu: Miyataka Shimizu (清水 都貴, Shimizu Miyataka) (born November 23, 1981 in Saitama Prefecture) is a Japanese former professional racing cyclist. After beginning cycling at Hatoyama High School, he attended the National Institute of Fitness and Sports in Kanoya before becoming a professional in 2004. Shimizu is in general considered an all-rounder. His victory at Paris–Corrèze in 2008, the first of a UCI category 1 stage race by a Japanese, has been termed "epoch making." In 2014, he was chosen to represent Japan at the 2014 UCI Road World Championships in the men's road race. He announced he would retire at the end of the 2014 season.
/wiki/Ludovic_Turpin: Ludovic Turpin (born 22 March 1975 in Laval) is a French professional road racing cyclist, who most recently competed for amateur team Vélo Club Grand Case.
/wiki/Bruno_Langlois: Bruno Langlois (born March 1, 1979) is a Canadian racing cyclist. Born in Matane, Quebec, Langlois began his professional career in 1999 with the Jet Fuel Coffee - Vitasoy cycling team.
/wiki/Junya_Sano: Junya Sano (佐野 淳哉, Sano Jun'ya, born January 9, 1982) is a Japanese road bicycle racer, who rides for the UCI Continental team Matrix Powertag.
/wiki/Klaas_Sys: Klaas Sys (born 30 November 1986) is a Belgian cyclist who last rode for the Josan-To Win Cycling Team.
/wiki/Carter_Jones: Carter Jones (born February 27, 1989) is an American former professional road racing cyclist, who rode professionally between 2010 and 2016 for the Jelly Belly–Kenda, Trek–Livestrong, Bissell, Optum–Kelly Benefit Strategies, and Team Giant–Alpecin teams.
/wiki/Edwin_S%C3%A1nchez_(cyclist): Edwin Sánchez Anzola (born 20 July 1983 in Caparrapi) is a Colombian cyclist riding for the Movistar Team América.
/wiki/Nicolas_Dumont: Nicolas Dumont (born 6 June 1940) is a Belgian water polo player. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics and the 1964 Summer Olympics.
/wiki/Miguel_Ubeto: Miguel Armando Ubeto Aponte (born 2 September 1976 in Caracas) is a male professional road racing cyclist from Venezuela. He turned professional in 2012 with Androni Giocattoli–Venezuela before signing with the UCI World Tour team Lampre–Merida for 2013. In 2011 he won the UCI America Tour.
/wiki/Flober_Pe%C3%B1a: José Flober Peña Peña (born February 7, 1974 in Paipa, Boyacá) is a professional road racing cyclist from Colombia. He was nicknamed "Donatelo" during his career.
/wiki/Martin_Pr%C3%A1zdnovsk%C3%BD: Martin Prázdnovský (born 22 October 1975 in Streda nad Bodrogom) is a Slovak former cyclist.
/wiki/Jos%C3%A9_Daniel_Bernal: José Daniel Bernal García (born March 15, 1973 in Bogotá) is a male road cyclist from Colombia.
/wiki/Andrey_Mizourov: Andrey Mizourov (Kazakh: Андрей Мизуров, born March 16, 1973 in Karaganda, Soviet Union, now Kazakhstan) is a former Kazakhstani  professional road bicycle racer.
/wiki/Alexander_Mironov: Alexander Mironov  (Russian: Александр Миронов; born 22 January 1984) is a Russian professional road bicycle racer, who last rode for UCI Professional Continental Team RusVelo. He is the 2005 under-23 national road race champion and the winner of 2010 Trofeo Franco Balestra. He turned professional in 2011, riding for the UCI ProTour team Team Katusha, but moved to RusVelo for the 2012 season.
